### 4. Implementation in a Server Component

Because of the RLS policy and the Prisma extension, it is **physically impossible** for this code to return projects belonging to another tenant, even if the developer forgets to add a `where` clause.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/projects/page.tsx
import { getTenantContext } from "@/lib/tenant-context";

export default async function ProjectsPage() {
  const { db, tenantId } = await getTenantContext();

  // Notice: No "where: { tenantId }" is manually required here.
  // The RLS policy handles it automatically!
  const projects = await db.project.findMany();

  return (
    <div className="p-8">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold">Projects for Tenant: {tenantId}</h1>
      <ul className="mt-4">
        {projects.map((p) => (
          <li key={p.id} className="border-b py-2">{p.name}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
}
