### 2. The Atomic Lua Script

This is the "secret sauce." By using Lua, Redis executes the check and the increment as a single atomic unit. No other request can intervene.

```lua
-- increment_and_check.lua
-- KEYS[1] = usage_key (e.g., "usage:tenant_123")
-- KEYS[2] = limit_key (e.g., "limit:tenant_123")
-- ARGV[1] = increment_amount

local current_usage = tonumber(redis.call('GET', KEYS[1]) or "0")
local limit = tonumber(redis.call('GET', KEYS[2]) or "0")
local increment = tonumber(ARGV[1])

if limit > 0 and (current_usage + increment) > limit then
    return -1 -- Over limit
else
    local new_usage = redis.call('INCRBY', KEYS[1], increment)
    return new_usage
end
```

