### 4. Persistence Worker (Sync Redis -> Postgres)

To ensure data isn't lost if Redis restarts and to provide long-term reporting, we run a background task.

```typescript
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client'; // or your choice of ORM
const prisma = new PrismaClient();

async function syncUsageToDb() {
  // 1. Get all tenants who had activity
  const tenantIds = await redis.smembers('tenants_to_sync');
  if (tenantIds.length === 0) return;

  for (const tenantId of tenantIds) {
    const usage = await redis.get(`usage:${tenantId}`);

    // 2. Batch update Postgres
    await prisma.tenant.update({
      where: { id: tenantId },
      data: { current_usage: BigInt(usage || '0') }
    });

    // 3. Remove from dirty set
    await redis.srem('tenants_to_sync', tenantId);
  }
}

// Run every 10 seconds
setInterval(syncUsageToDb, 10000);
```

