### 2. Implementing Row-Level Security (The "Shield")

We will use a PostgreSQL **Session Variable**. The application will tell the database "I am acting on behalf of Tenant A" at the start of every request.

```sql
-- 1. Enable RLS on the table
ALTER TABLE "Order" ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- 2. Create a policy: 
-- "Users can only see/edit rows where tenant_id matches the session variable"
CREATE POLICY order_isolation_policy ON "Order"
USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.current_tenant_id')::uuid)
WITH CHECK (tenant_id = current_setting('app.current_tenant_id')::uuid);
```

