### 2. Implementing Row-Level Security (RLS)

This is the most critical part. We will configure Postgres to enforce that a database connection can only see rows matching a specific `tenant_id`.

**SQL Migration (Run this in your DB):**
```sql
-- 1. Enable RLS on the table
ALTER TABLE projects ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- 2. Create a policy that checks a session variable
-- We will set 'app.current_tenant_id' in our code for every request
CREATE POLICY tenant_isolation_policy ON projects
USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.current_tenant_id'));

-- 3. Apply the same for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
CREATE POLICY tenant_update_policy ON projects
FOR ALL
TO authenticated
USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.current_tenant_id'))
WITH CHECK (tenant_id = current_setting('app.current_tenant_id'));
```

