### 1. The Redis Lua Script (`rate_limiter.lua`)
Using Lua ensures that the logic runs inside Redis. This is 10x faster and prevents "check-then-set" race conditions.

```lua
-- Keys: [tenant_key]
-- Args: [limit, window_in_seconds]

local limit = tonumber(ARGV[1])
local window = tonumber(ARGV[2])
local current = redis.call("INCR", KEYS[1])

if current == 1 then
    -- First request in this window, set expiration
    redis.call("EXPIRE", KEYS[1], window)
end

if current > limit then
    return -1 -- Limit exceeded
end

return limit - current -- Return remaining tokens
```

