### 3. Implementing "Fairness" with Concurrency Limits
Rate limiting handles *requests per minute*, but a "Massive Spike" often involves long-running requests that hog database connections. We can add a **Concurrency Limiter** to ensure one tenant doesn't take all the Express worker slots.

```javascript
// middleware/concurrency.js
const activeRequests = new Map();
const MAX_CONCURRENT_PER_TENANT = 5; 

const concurrencyLimiter = (req, res, next) => {
    const tenantId = req.header('x-tenant-id');
    const currentCount = activeRequests.get(tenantId) || 0;

    if (currentCount >= MAX_CONCURRENT_PER_TENANT) {
        return res.status(503).json({ 
            error: 'Server Busy', 
            message: 'Too many simultaneous requests for your tenant.' 
        });
    }

    activeRequests.set(tenantId, currentCount + 1);

    // Decrement when the request finishes
    res.on('finish', () => {
        const count = activeRequests.get(tenantId);
        activeRequests.set(tenantId, Math.max(0, count - 1));
    });

    next();
};

module.exports = concurrencyLimiter;
```

