### 4. Why this approach is better than a Cron Job

| Feature | Query-Time (This Solution) | Background Worker (Cron) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Complexity** | Very Low | High (Needs worker, queue, error handling) |
| **Precision** | Millisecond perfect | Depends on cron frequency (e.g., every 1 min) |
| **Reliability** | Inherently reliable (logic-based) | Can fail if worker crashes or queue backs up |
| **Database Load** | Negligible (with proper indexing) | High (Requires constant UPDATE writes) |

