### 2. Database Schema (Prisma)

We define a `Post` model. Notice we don't strictly need a `status` enum for visibility, though we keep one for "Draft" vs "Final" intent.

```prisma
// schema.prisma

model Post {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  title       String
  content     String   @db.Text

  // The core of scheduling
  publishedAt DateTime 

  // Intent status: Allows an author to keep a post private 
  // even if the publishedAt date has passed.
  isDraft     Boolean  @default(false)

  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([publishedAt]) // Critical for performance
}
