### 1. Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

We need a flexible structure. We use `jsonb` for `rules` and `content` to allow different groups to store different types of data without migrating the schema every time a new hobby is added.

```sql
-- Groups table defining the "Type" of community
CREATE TABLE groups (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  slug TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  template_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'PHOTOGRAPHY', 'WRITING', 'MARKETPLACE'
  rules JSONB NOT NULL,        -- Array of rule objects
  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Posts table with flexible content
CREATE TABLE posts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  group_id UUID REFERENCES groups(id),
  author_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  content JSONB NOT NULL,      -- Stores {image_url: '...'} or {body: '...'}
  metadata JSONB,              -- EXIF data for photos, Word count for writing
  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
);
