              <CardContent className="p-4 flex gap-4">
                {item.metadata.type === 'link' ? <LinkIcon className="text-blue-500" /> : <FileText className="text-orange-500" />}
                <p className="text-sm line-clamp-3">{item.content}</p>
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          ))}
        </div>

        {/* Semantic Sidebar */}
        <div className="space-y-4">
          <h2 className="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground flex items-center gap-2">
            <Sparkles size={14} className="text-yellow-500" /> Related Context
          </h2>
          {related.length === 0 && <p className="text-xs text-muted-foreground italic">Add something to see connections...</p>}
          {related.map((item) => (
            <div key={item.id} className="p-3 rounded-lg bg-secondary/50 border text-xs space-y-2">
              <p className="line-clamp-2">{item.content}</p>
              <div className="text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">
                Match: {Math.round(item.similarity * 100)}%
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  )
}
```

### 5. Why this works for a "Second Brain"

1.  **Semantic Search (The Magic):** We aren't using `LIKE %query%`. By using OpenAI's `text-embedding-3-small`, the app understands that a note about "The Roman Empire" is related to a YouTube link about "Ancient History."
2.  **Unstructured Data:** You don't need folders or tags. The AI handles the "organization" by calculating the distance between vectors in 1536-dimensional space.
3.  **Low Latency:** Supabase's `pgvector` allows us to perform "Vector Similarity Search" directly inside the database, which is extremely fast for personal use.

### 6. Production Enhancements to add next:
*   **Link Scraping:** In the `saveMemory` action, use a library like `cheerio` or `link-preview-js`. If the input is a URL, fetch the website title and description to include in the embedding. This makes the "related" feature much more accurate for web links.
*   **Video Transcription:** If a YouTube URL is added, you could use an API to grab the transcript and embed the text of the video.
*   **Authentication:** Add Supabase Auth so different users can have their own private "brains."

