### 5. Handling Scaling with Redis

In a production environment, users editing the same document might be connected to different server instances. We use Redis Pub/Sub to sync updates between servers.

Modify the `ydoc.on('update', ...)` block to include Redis:

```typescript
import { createClient } from 'redis';

const pub = createClient();
const sub = createClient();

// Inside the persistence bindState
ydoc.on('update', (update, origin) => {
  // 1. Save to DB (as shown before)
  persistence.storeUpdate(docName, update);

  // 2. If the update came from a local WS connection, broadcast to other servers
  if (origin !== 'redis') {
    pub.publish(`doc-updates:${docName}`, Buffer.from(update).toString('base64'));
  }
});

// Subscribe to Redis updates
sub.subscribe(`doc-updates:${docName}`, (message) => {
  const update = Buffer.from(message, 'base64');
  Y.applyUpdate(ydoc, update, 'redis'); // 'redis' origin prevents infinite loop
});
```

