### 6. Version History

To implement version history, we can snapshot the document state whenever a "milestone" is reached (e.g., every 5 minutes or manually by the user).

```typescript
app.post('/documents/:id/version', async (req, reply) => {
  const { id } = req.params as any;
  const ydoc = await persistence.getYDoc(id);
  const snapshot = Y.encodeStateAsUpdate(ydoc);

  await pool.query(
    'INSERT INTO document_versions (doc_id, data, label) VALUES ($1, $2, $3)',
    [id, Buffer.from(snapshot), req.body.label]
  );

  return { success: true };
});
```

