### 4. Real-time Leaderboard Update (The 10s Broadcast)

We use a Goroutine to fetch the Top 100 and publish them to a WebSocket hub or a Redis Pub/Sub channel every 10 seconds.

```go
func (s *EngagementStore) BroadcastLeaderboard() {
	ticker := time.NewTicker(10 * time.Second)
	for range ticker.C {
		top100, err := s.GetTopTrending()
		if err != nil {
			continue
		}
		// Push to WebSocket Hub or Frontend Cache
		fmt.Println("Broadcasting Live Top 100...")
		for rank, post := range top100 {
			_ = rank // Publish: Rank, PostID, Score
		}
	}
}
```

